description.narrative: By the end of 2019, at least 75% of children and adolescents enrolled in prioritized educational institutions belonging to the subsystem of Basic Education improve their attendance and stay in school, which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2019, UNICEF will have contributed to ensuring that children and adolescents (particularly the most excluded) are attending and remaining within educational facilities and that these latter are improving their quality of teaching and educational content, using a rights, gender, adolescent development, intercultural and bilingual approach.
